The Kano Police headquarters situated at Bompai, Nasarawa Local Government, is reported to be on fire, with many offices and files suspected to be burnt to ashes. The State Fire Service are set to have since deployed to the scene to contain the raging fire on the one-storey building of the command. Unconfirmed reports have it that the entire upstairs was caught up with fire except the office of the State Police Commissioner, Mamman Dauda, which is highly fortified. Although the Command spokesman, SP Abdullahi Haruna Kiyawa phone was switched off at the time of this report, but sources said the cause of the inferno could not be immediately verified.